---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navigation from '../components/Navigation.astro';

const title = "Story & Lore - Escape From Pizzeria Dark Secrets";
const description = "Discover the dark history and hidden lore of Escape From Pizzeria. Character backgrounds, timeline of events, and analysis of the game's mysterious story elements.";
const keywords = "Escape From Pizzeria story, Escape From Pizzeria lore, pizzeria history, game story analysis, horror game backstory";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} keywords={keywords}>
	<Navigation />
	
	<main class="lore-page">
		<div class="container">
			<!-- Header -->
			<header class="page-header">
				<h1>The Dark History of Freddy's Pizzeria</h1>
				<p class="page-subtitle">Uncover the Truth Behind the Horror</p>
				<div class="atmospheric-quote">
					"Some places are born evil. Others become evil through the actions of those who inhabit them. 
					Freddy's Pizzeria... was both."
				</div>
			</header>

			<!-- Timeline -->
			<section class="timeline-section">
				<h2>üìÖ Timeline of Events</h2>
				<div class="timeline">
					<div class="timeline-item">
						<div class="timeline-date">1987</div>
						<div class="timeline-content">
							<h3>The Grand Opening</h3>
							<p>Freddy's Family Pizzeria opens its doors with great fanfare. Owner Marcus Fredrickson promises "the most magical dining experience for families." The restaurant quickly becomes popular with local families.</p>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="timeline-item">
						<div class="timeline-date">1989</div>
						<div class="timeline-content">
							<h3>The First Incident</h3>
							<p>A child goes missing during a birthday party. Security footage shows the child entering the kitchen area but never leaving. The case remains unsolved, and the restaurant continues operating.</p>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="timeline-item">
						<div class="timeline-date">1991</div>
						<div class="timeline-content">
							<h3>The Night Shift</h3>
							<p>Strange reports from night security guards begin. Sounds of children playing after hours, animatronics moving on their own, and unexplained cold spots throughout the building.</p>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="timeline-item">
						<div class="timeline-date">1993</div>
						<div class="timeline-content">
							<h3>The Investigation</h3>
							<p>Police investigate the basement after reports of foul odors. They find evidence of disturbing activities but Marcus Fredrickson disappears before he can be arrested.</p>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="timeline-item">
						<div class="timeline-date">1994</div>
						<div class="timeline-content">
							<h3>The Closure</h3>
							<p>Freddy's Pizzeria officially closes. The building is abandoned, but locals report seeing lights and hearing sounds from inside. The property becomes known as cursed.</p>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="timeline-item">
						<div class="timeline-date">Present</div>
						<div class="timeline-content">
							<h3>Your Arrival</h3>
							<p>You enter the abandoned pizzeria, unaware of its dark history. The spirits of the past are waiting, and they have unfinished business...</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- Characters -->
			<section class="characters-section">
				<h2>üë• Key Characters</h2>
				<div class="characters-grid">
					<div class="character-card">
						<div class="character-avatar">üë®‚Äçüíº</div>
						<h3>Marcus Fredrickson</h3>
						<p class="character-role">Owner & Primary Antagonist</p>
						<p>The charismatic owner of Freddy's Pizzeria who hid a dark secret. His obsession with "preserving childhood innocence" led him down a twisted path. Disappeared in 1993 before his arrest.</p>
						<div class="character-details">
							<strong>Last Known Location:</strong> Unknown<br>
							<strong>Status:</strong> Missing, Presumed Dead<br>
							<strong>Legacy:</strong> The evil that still haunts the pizzeria
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="character-card">
						<div class="character-avatar">üëÆ</div>
						<h3>Detective Sarah Chen</h3>
						<p class="character-role">Lead Investigator</p>
						<p>The detective who led the investigation into the pizzeria's crimes. Her case files, scattered throughout the building, reveal the full extent of the horror that occurred here.</p>
						<div class="character-details">
							<strong>Badge Number:</strong> 5683<br>
							<strong>Status:</strong> Retired<br>
							<strong>Note:</strong> Her badge number is the safe combination
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="character-card">
						<div class="character-avatar">üëª</div>
						<h3>The Lost Children</h3>
						<p class="character-role">Trapped Spirits</p>
						<p>The innocent victims whose spirits remain trapped within the pizzeria. They appear throughout the game, sometimes helping, sometimes hindering your escape.</p>
						<div class="character-details">
							<strong>Count:</strong> Seven confirmed victims<br>
							<strong>Ages:</strong> 6-12 years old<br>
							<strong>Manifestation:</strong> Cold spots, whispers, moving objects
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="character-card">
						<div class="character-avatar">ü§ñ</div>
						<h3>Freddy the Bear</h3>
						<p class="character-role">Possessed Animatronic</p>
						<p>The main mascot of the pizzeria, now possessed by malevolent spirits. Freddy serves as the primary threat during your escape, hunting you through the dark corridors.</p>
						<div class="character-details">
							<strong>Height:</strong> 6'2"<br>
							<strong>Behavior:</strong> Aggressive, Unpredictable<br>
							<strong>Weakness:</strong> Bright lights temporarily stun him
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- Locations -->
			<section class="locations-section">
				<h2>üè¢ Key Locations</h2>
				<div class="locations-grid">
					<div class="location-card">
						<h3>üçΩÔ∏è Main Dining Area</h3>
						<p>Once filled with laughter and celebration, now a haunting reminder of happier times. The tables remain set as if waiting for guests who will never return.</p>
						<div class="location-secrets">
							<strong>Hidden Secrets:</strong> Newspaper clipping under table 13, employee photos behind the counter
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="location-card">
						<h3>üçï Kitchen</h3>
						<p>The heart of the restaurant's operations, now a maze of rusted equipment and dark corners. The freezer holds more than just old food...</p>
						<div class="location-secrets">
							<strong>Hidden Secrets:</strong> Secret recipe in UV ink, crowbar in freezer, basement key in oven
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="location-card">
						<h3>üï≥Ô∏è The Basement</h3>
						<p>The darkest part of the pizzeria, both literally and figuratively. This is where Marcus conducted his twisted experiments and where the truth lies buried.</p>
						<div class="location-secrets">
							<strong>Hidden Secrets:</strong> Security footage, hidden room behind false wall, evidence locker
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="location-card">
						<h3>üè¢ Manager's Office</h3>
						<p>Marcus's private domain, filled with disturbing documents and personal effects. The safe here contains the most damning evidence of his crimes.</p>
						<div class="location-secrets">
							<strong>Hidden Secrets:</strong> Safe with evidence, emergency exit key card, personal diary
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- Mysteries -->
			<section class="mysteries-section">
				<h2>üîç Unsolved Mysteries</h2>
				<div class="mystery-grid">
					<div class="mystery-card">
						<h3>‚ùì The Seventh Child</h3>
						<p>While six victims have been identified, evidence suggests a seventh child went missing. Their identity remains unknown, and their spirit seems different from the others - more powerful, more angry.</p>
					</div>

					<div class="mystery-card">
						<h3>‚ùì The Ritual Circle</h3>
						<p>Strange symbols found in the hidden basement room suggest Marcus was involved in occult practices. Were the disappearances part of some dark ritual?</p>
					</div>

					<div class="mystery-card">
						<h3>‚ùì The Time Loop</h3>
						<p>Some players report experiencing the same events multiple times. Is the pizzeria trapped in a temporal loop, doomed to repeat its tragic history?</p>
					</div>

					<div class="mystery-card">
						<h3>‚ùì The Other Locations</h3>
						<p>References in documents suggest Marcus owned other properties. Are there more pizzerias with similar dark histories? The investigation continues...</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- Theories -->
			<section class="theories-section">
				<h2>üß† Fan Theories</h2>
				<div class="theory-list">
					<div class="theory-item">
						<h3>Theory 1: The Possession Theory</h3>
						<p>The animatronics aren't just haunted - they're possessed by the spirits of the missing children. Each animatronic represents one victim, explaining their different behaviors and personalities.</p>
						<div class="theory-evidence">
							<strong>Evidence:</strong> Seven missing children, seven animatronics found in basement storage
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="theory-item">
						<h3>Theory 2: The Parallel Universe Theory</h3>
						<p>The pizzeria exists in multiple dimensions simultaneously. The "time loop" experiences are actually glimpses into alternate versions of events.</p>
						<div class="theory-evidence">
							<strong>Evidence:</strong> Inconsistent newspaper dates, objects appearing and disappearing
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="theory-item">
						<h3>Theory 3: The Survivor Theory</h3>
						<p>Marcus didn't disappear - he's still alive, hiding somewhere in the pizzeria's extensive underground tunnels, continuing his twisted work.</p>
						<div class="theory-evidence">
							<strong>Evidence:</strong> Fresh food in freezer, recent security footage, unexplained sounds
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- Easter Eggs Analysis -->
			<section class="easter-eggs-section">
				<h2>ü•ö Easter Eggs & Hidden Messages</h2>
				<div class="easter-egg-list">
					<div class="easter-egg-item">
						<h3>The Developer's Message</h3>
						<p>The first letter of each chapter title spells out "HELP" - a cry for assistance from the trapped spirits, or a message from the game's creators?</p>
					</div>

					<div class="easter-egg-item">
						<h3>The Real-World Connection</h3>
						<p>The pizzeria's address (1987 Freddy Lane) references several real-world incidents involving family restaurants in the 1980s.</p>
					</div>

					<div class="easter-egg-item">
						<h3>The Hidden Sequel Hook</h3>
						<p>In the secret ending, a newspaper headline mentions "Similar Incidents at Sister Location" - hinting at potential future games in the series.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>
		</div>
	</main>
</Layout>

